Robert ROGERS, Libelant Appellant, v. Pennsylvania Railroad Lighter No. 219, Her Tackle, etc.; Pennsylvania Railroad Company, Claimant Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 19, 1926.) No. 318. Park, Mattison & Lynch and Frank P. Treanor, Jr., all of New York City, for appellant. Burlingham, Veeder, Masten & Fearey, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Frederic Conger, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
